sider.com%2F67f93731a466d2b74ab2ef1b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20wild%20moves%20in%20the%20bond%20market%20are%20stoking%20concerns%20about%20volatility%20in%20other%20risk%20assets.%3Cp%3EAP%2FRichard%20Drew%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EWe%20don't%20think%20risk%20assets%20can%20stabilize%20until%20the%20bond%20market%20does%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Barclays'%20Rajadhyaksha%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BPerhaps%20the%20events%20of%20this%20week%20were%20a%20one-off.%20And%20perhaps%20a%20deal%20is%20announced%20over%20the%20weekend%20that%20lifts%20sentiment%2C%20widens%20swap%20spreads%2C%20and%20causes%20longer%20US%20rates%20to%20rally%20and%20the%20USD%20to%20strengthen.%20But%20unless%20those%20things%20happen%20consistently%20for%20at%20least%20a%20few%20days%20%E2%80%94%20until%20US%20Treasuries%20go%20back%20to%20behaving%20the%20way%20they%20are%20supposed%20to%20%E2%80%94%20we%20would%20be%20very%20cautious%20on%20all%20risk%20assets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBond%20investors%20should%20stay%20vigilant%2C%26quot%3B%20Matt%20Egan%2C%20a%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20Loomis%2C%20Sayles%20%26amp%3B%20Company%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20recent%20price%20action%20suggests%20that%20the%20US%20Treasury%20market%20itself%20could%20become%20a%20source%20of%20instability%E2%80%94a%20risk%20that%20now%20feels%20more%20plausible%20than%20remote.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20if%20investors%20are%20unwilling%20to%20buy%20as%20much%20government%20debt%2C%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20funding%20problem%20for%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20relies%20on%20investors%20purchasing%20debt%20securities%20to%20finance%20its%20activity%20%E2%80%94%20and%20there's%20around%20%243%20trillion%20in%20US%20Treasury%20debt%20set%20to%20mature%20this%20year%20that%20will%20need%20to%20be%20refinanced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Treasury%20Building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f937da3fe8d3928362d66e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDemand%20at%20the%2010-year%20and%2030-year%20US%20Treasury%20auctions%20was%20strong%20this%20week.%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20hasn't%20happened%20yet.%20Demand%20for%20the%2010-year%20and%2030-year%20US%20Treasurys%20was%20robust%20in%20auctions%20this%20week%2C%20with%20the%20government%20issuing%20%2422%20billion%20in%2030-year%20bonds%20and%20%2439%20billion%20in%2010-year%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20for%20a%20brief%20moment%2C%20the%20market%20was%20veering%20into%20dangerous%20territory%2C%20top%20economist%20Mohamed%20El-Erian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20came%20very%20close%20today%20to%20the%20line%20that%20separates%20wild%20market%20movement%20in%20the%20bond%20market%20to%20market%20dysfunction%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20chief%20economist%20advisor%20of%20Allianz%2C%20said%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20pointing%20to%20concerns%20about%20liquidity%20in%20markets.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20to%20get%20there%20again.%20Because%20the%20more%20you%20get%20to%20that%20point%20repeatedly%2C%20the%20higher%20risk%20you're%20going%20to%20cross%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbond-yields-sell-off-trump-tariffs-trade-war-us-debt-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744444802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f951a43fe8d3928362de2e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbond-yields-sell-off-trump-tariffs-trade-war-us-debt-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20stock%20market%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20this%20week%2C%20but%20the%20bigger%20story%20was%20going%20on%20in%20the%20debt%20market