t%20susceptible%20to%20political%20instability%2C%20economic%20decline%20and%20invasion%20from%20foreign%20enemies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20study%2C%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.geoscienceworld.org%2Fgsa%2Fgeology%2Farticle-abstract%2Fdoi%2F10.1130%2FG53168.1%2F653479%2FGreenlandic-debris-in-Iceland-likely-tied-to-Bond%3FredirectedFrom%3Dfulltext%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EGeology%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20states%20that%20a%20small%20period%20of%20intense%20cooling%20called%20the%20Late%20Antique%20Little%20Ice%20Age%20(LALIA)%20finally%20led%20to%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20empire%20in%201453%20CE.%20Researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southampton%20found%20that%20the%20ice%20age%20may%20have%20been%20triggered%20by%20volcanic%20ash%20from%20three%20massive%20eruptions%20that%20blocked%20out%20sunlight%20and%20lowered%20global%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Roman%20Empire%2C%20this%20climate%20shift%20may%20have%20been%20the%20straw%20that%20broke%20the%20camel's%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.southampton.ac.uk%2Fnews%2F2025%2F04%2Fancient-rocks-reveal-how-ice-age-weakened-the-roman-empire.page%23%3A~%3Atext%3DScientists%2520at%2520the%2520University%2520of%2Ccollapse%2520of%2520the%2520Roman%2520Empire.%5C%22%3Esaid%20%3C%2Fa%3ETom%20Gernon%2C%20Professor%20of%20Earth%20Science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southampton%20and%20co-author%20of%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20event%20led%20to%20temperatures%20plummeting%20across%20Europe%20which%20led%20to%20widespread%20crop%20failures%2C%20increased%20livestock%20mortality%2C%20and%20a%20sharp%20rise%20in%20food%20prices.%20Ultimately%2C%20it%20led%20to%20illness%20and%20famine%20across%20the%20Roman%20Empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fgang-of-60-killer-whales-attack-and-devour-pygmy-blue-whale-in-brutal-video-8145308%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20Gang%20Of%2060%20Killer%20Whales%20Attack%20And%20Devour%20Pygmy%20Blue%20Whale%20In%20Brutal%20Video%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Christopher%20Spencer%2C%20one%20of%20the%20lead%20authors%20of%20the%20research%2C%20said%20his%20team%20also%20analysed%20the%20age%20and%20composition%20of%20the%20rocks%20found%20on%20a%20raised%20beach%20terrace%20on%20Iceland's%20west%20coast%20to%20gather%20geologic%20evidence%20for%20their%20hypothesis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20knew%20these%20rocks%20seemed%20somewhat%20out%20of%20place%20because%20the%20rock%20types%20are%20unlike%20anything%20found%20in%20Iceland%20today%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20know%20where%20they%20came%20from.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20in%20286%20AD%2C%20Ancient%20Rome%20was%20split%20into%20two%20parts%3A%20the%20Western%20Empire%20and%20the%20Eastern%20Empire.%20While%20the%20former%20had%20already%20fallen%20by%20the%20time%20the%20climactic%20shift%20began%2C%20the%20latter%20faced%20a%20significant%20impact%20due%20to%20a%20global%20drop%20in%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20involved%20examination%20of%20tiny%20mineral%20crystals%20called%20zircons%2C%20locked%20inside%20the%20rocks%2C%20which%20enabled%20the%20team%20to%20pinpoint%20their%20source.%20The%20findings%20indicated%20that%20the%20rocks%20were%20brought%20to%20this%20location%20by%20drifting%20icebergs%20during%20the%20LALIA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20suggests%20that%20the%20LALIA%20could%20have%20put%20significant%20strain%20on%20the%20Eastern%20Roman%20Empire%20and%20adds%20to%20a%20growing%20body%20of%20evidence%20pointing%20to%20its%20role%20in%20the%20empire's%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744432980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F23hn7g6o_as_625x300_12_April_25.jpg%