0Mobility%20executive%20Agust%C3%ADn%20Escobar%2C%20his%20wife%2C%20and%20three%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pilot%2C%20who%20the%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board%20said%20on%20Friday%20had%20about%20788%20hours%20of%20total%20flight%20experience%2C%20also%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2021-year-old%20Bell%20206%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-people-new-york-city-helicopter-commute-avoid-cars-traffic-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelicopter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20registered%20N216MH%20and%20operated%20by%20New%20York%20Helicopter%2C%20plummeted%20into%20the%20river%20off%20the%20New%20Jersey%20shoreline%20at%20around%203%3A15%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20crashed%20upside%20down%20after%20what%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20a%20midair%20breakup.%20The%20aircraft%20was%20owned%20by%20Louisiana-based%20Meridian%20Helicopters%2C%20LLC%2C%20whose%20website%20says%20it%20sells%2C%20refurbishes%2C%20and%20leases%20helicopters.%20Meridian%20didn't%20return%20an%20email%20or%20phone%20message%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20military%20helicopter%20pilot%20Brian%20Alexander%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20accident%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20a%20result%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bcatastrophic%20mechanical%20failure%26quot%3B%20involving%20both%20the%20main%20and%20tail%20rotors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20no%20cause%20is%20confirmed%20and%20people%20should%20wait%20for%20the%20NTSB's%20investigation%20before%20jumping%20to%20conclusions.%20Alexander%20also%20is%20a%20partner%20at%20aviation%20accident%20law%20firm%20Kreindler%20%26amp%3B%20Kreindler.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Thursday's%20helicopter%20crash%20could%20spark%20renewed%20fears%20amid%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdc-plane-crash-timeline-atc-american-airlines-helicopter-collision-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20spat%20of%20airline%20accidents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20cause%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20related.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ee11b4e7-0586-4f47-a725-e903f11e73f1%5C%22%3EWhy%20did%20the%20helicopter%20crash%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVideos%20posted%20on%20social%20media%20show%20the%20helicopter's%20rotary%20systems%20apparently%20detached%20mid-flight%2C%20falling%20into%20the%20water%20after%20the%20aircraft's%20main%20body%20had%20already%20crashed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20say%20which%20came%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexander%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20appears%20to%20be%20spinning%2C%20which%20would%20suggest%20a%20tail%20rotor%20issue%2C%20but%20you%20can't%20rule%20out%20a%20main%20rotor%20detaching%20first%20and%20hitting%20the%20tail%20rotor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spinning%20he's%20referring%20to%20is%20the%20helicopter%20fuselage%20as%20it%20fell%20into%20the%20Hudson%2C%20which%20he%20said%20means%20the%20tail%20rotor%20likely%20failed%20at%20some%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%20that%20without%20a%20tail%20rotor%2C%20the%20helicopter%20would%20%26quot%3Bspin%20like%20a%20top%26quot%3B%20due%20to%20the%20torque%20created%20by%20the%20main%20rotor%20as%20it%20produces%20lift%20and%20thrust.%20Either%20or%20both%20systems%20failing%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdc-plane-crash-military-training-congested-airspace-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elead%20to%20an%20accident%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20lose%20your%20main%20rotor%2C%20meaning%20it's%20detached%2C%20you%20have%20no%20lift%2C%20you're%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexander%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20you%20can%20do%20at%20that%20point%3B%20you're%20just%20a%20falling%20object.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20a%20helicopter%20that%20loses%20just%20a%20tail%20rotor%20is%20a%20severe%20situation%2C%20but%20it%20can%20still%20be%20flown%20%E2%80%94%20though%20with%20great%20difficulty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Map%20of%20the%20crash%20site.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f97132c6ad288d147dfd09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223375%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Bell%20206%20helicopter%20took%20off%20from%20the%20downtown%20Manhattan%20Wall%20Street%20Heliport%20in%20New%20York%20at%20about%202%3A50%20p.m.%20for%20a%20sightseeing%20flight.%3Cp%3EYasin%20Demirci%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%20said%20that%20losing%20power%20is%20typically%20a%20more%20surmountable%20issue.%20In%20a%20scenario%20where%20the%20helicopter's%20engine%20failed%2C%20and%20the%20blades%20were%20still%20attached%2C%20the%20aircraft%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelicopter-landing-auto-rotation-physics-video-2016-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eauto-rotate%20to%20descend%20to%20land%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENTSB%20Chairman%20Jennifer%20Homendy%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20part%20of%20the%20wreckage%20had%20been%20pulled%20from%20the%20river%2C%20but%20dive%20teams%20are%20still%20retrieving%20components%2C%20including%20the%20main%20and%20tail%20rotors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20agency%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20speculate%26quot%3B%20on%20probable%20cause%20and%20still%20needed%20to%20gather%20the%20sunken%20components%2C%20conduct%20witness%20interviews%2C%20and%20gather%20records%20like%20maintenance%20logs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2220b72e8f-1bf5-45ce-b367-bba79f6a6eec%5C%22%3EWhy%20did%20the%20rotors%20apparently%20detach%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%20said%20that%20there%20are%20several%20reasons%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-flew-in-helicopter-for-first-time-ever-heliflite-review-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelicopter%3C%2Fa%3E%20rotors%20could%20detach%2C%20like%20mechanic%20error%20or%20a%20transmission%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20the%20mast%20